articles.author: Gram Slattery, David Lawder
articles.description: Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump was safe on Sunday after the Secret Service foiled what the FBI called an apparent assassination attempt while he was golfing on his course in West Palm Beach, Florida.
articles.title: Trump safe after new assassination attempt thwarted at Florida golf course

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: More rivers in central Europe spilled their banks on Monday in flooding that has killed at least 10 people from Poland to Romania and left many towns submerged or hit by gushing, debris-filled waters after days of heavy rainfalls.
articles.title: More rivers spill banks in central European floods, death toll rises

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Germany reintroduced temporary controls on its western and northern borders on Monday as part of efforts to combat irregular migration and cross-border crime, the interior ministry said.
articles.title: Germany's tighter border controls take effect, irking neighbours

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia launched its eighth air attack in September on Kyiv overnight, with air defence units destroying nearly 20 drones that were heading towards the country's capital, Ukrainian military said on Monday.
articles.title: Russia launches drone attack on Kyiv, Ukraine's military says

articles.author: Anastasiia Malenko, Pavel Polityuk
articles.description: Ryan Routh, the reported suspect in an apparent assassination attempt on Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump on Sunday, stayed in Kyiv in the summer of 2022 to encourage people to fight for Ukraine, he told a news outlet that year.
articles.title: Ryan Routh, reported suspect in Trump assassination attempt, backed Ukraine in war

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Kremlin said on Monday that the Ukrainian links of the alleged shooter in the assassination attempt on former U.S. President Donald Trump showed that "playing with fire" had consequences.
articles.title: Kremlin on alleged Trump shooter's Ukrainian links: playing with fire has consequences

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Typhoon Bebinca made landfall in Shanghai on Monday morning as a Category 1 storm, the most powerful tropical cyclone to directly hit the Chinese financial hub in more than seven decades.
articles.title: Typhoon Bebinca lands in Shanghai, strongest storm to hit city since 1949

articles.author: Lisa Richwine, Danielle Broadway
articles.description: The "Shogun" wins helped FX owner Walt Disney earn 60 Emmys this year, the most in the company's history.
articles.title: 'Shogun' wins best drama, 'Hacks' surprises in comedy at TV's Emmys

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Warships of Russia's Pacific Fleet and the Chinese Navy practiced missile and artillery firing in the Sea of ​​Japan as part of the Ocean-2024 drills, Russia's RIA state news agency reported on Monday.
articles.title: Russian and Chinese warships practice missile firing at Ocean-2024, RIA reports

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israeli Defence Minister Yoav Gallant told U.S. Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin on Monday that the window was closing for a diplomatic solution to the standoff with the Iranian-backed Hezbollah movement in southern Lebanon.
articles.title: Israeli minister says time running out for diplomatic solution with Hezbollah in Lebanon
